               <item n="project_comment_old">&lt;p&gt;[[Broomhead I]]: 180 has notes and translates: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a1 The monk came up to Upāli, having looked on high himself ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a2 || In Yaśodharavilāp metre || Surely regal pride ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a3 ... in order to destroy completely the fame [and good name] of the Śākyas. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b1 ... [the] good form [is] ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b2 Be not depressed O worthy ones! &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b3 ... in this manner they began to ... the feet of the saṅgha. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b4 They were ready as they saw the Śākyas [and presented] a garland of flowers. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;[[Broomhead I]]: 179 - this ms. and [[IOL Toch 73]] written in the same ductus.&lt;/p&gt;</item>
